{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Nt6Mi-fMSvzg"},"source":["\n","\n","## Graduation Project: **LinkedIn- Improving Hiring Efficiency**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"3Jh7wpEmUfIj"},"source":["# **Business Problem Overview**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"foCktmcaV6j8"},"source":["LinkedIn: Improving Hiring Efficiency\n","\n","LinkedIn is the world’s largest professional network, bringing together millions of job seekers, recruiters, and employers across industries. Every day, companies post thousands of roles, from entry-level positions to executive openings aiming to find the right candidates quickly and efficiently.\n","\n","As the platform continues to grow, LinkedIn’s leadership wants to go beyond increasing the number of job listings. The new focus is on **Improving Hiring Efficiency** - helping employers attract suitable candidates faster, with the right mix of salary, role clarity, and visibility. It reflects how effectively a job post converts visibility into actual applicant interest, given its title, location, company size, and compensation. By improving efficiency, LinkedIn can enhance recruiter success rates, candidate satisfaction, and overall platform engagement.\n","\n","LinkedIn believes that the answers lie hidden within its job listing data on factors such as:\n","\n","* which job titles, industries, or locations attract the highest\n","applicant volumes,\n","* how salary levels and benefits influence applicant interest,\n","whether company size or organization type affects job response,\n","* which seniority levels or employment types see the most efficient hiring outcomes.\n","\n","Objective\n","\n","In this project, we aim to analyze Linkedin analytics data to analyze:\n","\n","\n","*   **Measure Hiring Efficiency**: Understand how effectively Job postings convert visibility (views) into applicants interests\n","*   **Identify key influencing factors**: How job title, location, seniority level, work type, salary, and remote options impact applicants response\n","* **Compare performances across segments**: Why certain Posts, industries, roles attracts more applicants as compared to others\n","* **Provide Improvement Recommendations**: Actionable insights for recruiters so that they can optimize job postings to attract the right candidates faster.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"3HQ7bxVOdYlF"},"source":["Business Impact\n","\n","LinkedIn, hiring teams, and recruiters will benefit from this analysis in the following ways:\n","\n","* Enhance the **effectiveness of job postings** by emphasizing the features that attract candidates.\n","\n","* By concentrating on positions and tactics that **continuously generate greater applicant interest**, you can shorten the time to hire.\n","\n","* **Promote more aligned and transparent job opportunities** to improve the candidate experience.\n","\n","* **Help LinkedIn optimize its platform** by providing information to ranking algorithms so that more relevant job postings appear.\n","\n","Better job-candidate matching, quicker hiring results, and increased LinkedIn engagement are all facilitated by this project's understanding of what drives the hiring efficiency."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"etM5ANHTesGk"},"source":["# **Dataset Overview**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ij2_FtlvfNk7"},"source":["Dataset Overview\n","\n","* Dataset Name: Linkedin Analytics Dataset\n","* Number of Rows: 123,849\n","* Number of Columns: 31\n","* Description: The dataset captures key metrics for Linkedin Job Posting across various Industries, Locations and Seniority Levels, providing insights hiring efficiency, applicant interest and recruiters success across segments. Each row represents metrics for a different Job Posting."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2VVlWbdKpdcU"},"source":["**Column Definitions**\n","\n","1. job_id – Unique id to each Job post\n","2. company_name – Name of the company posting the job\n","3. title – Job Title\n","4. description – Details about Job Roles\n","5. max_salary – Upper range of Salary being offered\n","6. min_salary – Lower range of Salary being offered\n","7. med_salary – Median Salary derived from salary range\n","8. pay_period – Indicates whether salary is Weekly, Monthly or Yearly\n","9. normalized_salary – Salary converted to a standard annualized value for comparison.\n","10. currency – Currency type used in salary fields (e.g., USD).\n","11. compensation_type – Describes what the salary covers (e.g., base pay).\n","12. location – The primary location of the job posting.\n","13. zip_code – Postal code extracted from the location.\n","14. fips – US county code used for mapping or geographic analysis.\n","15. company_id – Numeric ID of the company posting the job\n","16. views – Number of times the job post was viewed.\n","17. applies – Total number of applications submitted for the job.\n","18. formatted_work_type – Employment type in human-readable format (e.g., Full-time, Contract).\n","19. work_type – Canonical employment type (system code). (e.g. FULL_TIME)\n","20. formatted_experience_level – Required seniority or experience level for the role.\n","21. remote_allowed – Binary flag showing if remote work is permitted (1 = yes, 0 = no).\n","22. sponsored – shows if job posting is sponsored or not;Paid promotion flag.\n","23. application_type – Specifies where candidates apply (LinkedIn or external site).\n","24. application_url – Link to the external application page (if applicable).\n","25. job_posting_url – Public LinkedIn URL for the job posting.\n","26. original_listed_time – When the job first went live (epoch milliseconds).\n","27. listed_time – Current/last observed listed time (epoch ms; often same as original_listed_time).\n","28. expiry – Scheduled expiration time of the job post.\n","29. closed_time – Actual time when the job post was closed or filled.\n","30. posting_domain – Domain of the platform hosting the application (e.g., linkedin.com).\n","31. skills_desc – Extracted or parsed keywords/skills mentioned in the description."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"BjGICAUAXk6d"},"source":["# **Analysis & Visualization !**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## ***1. Importing and Cleaning Data***"],"metadata":{"id":"ScDsy-O6bpeo"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Importing Necessary Libraries"],"metadata":{"id":"G1pFwzNkb2tj"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"o7LH6HTKfElJ"},"outputs":[],"source":["import pandas as pd"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"QPIyjtuQfHms"},"outputs":[],"source":["import pandas as pd  # For data manipulation and analysis\n","import numpy as np  # For numerical computations\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  # For plotting and visualization\n","import seaborn as sns  # For advanced visualizations"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"gkR8u19P704p"},"source":["### Loading Dataset from Google Drive"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":34418,"status":"ok","timestamp":1764436023305,"user":{"displayName":"Pran S","userId":"15779970413069318186"},"user_tz":-330},"id":"FvTtH2f8co6a","outputId":"928df27d-fe94-49de-af8c-ea02d8f17ae6","collapsed":true},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Requirement already satisfied: gdown in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (5.2.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: beautifulsoup4 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from gdown) (4.13.5)\n","Requirement already satisfied: filelock in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from gdown) (3.20.0)\n","Requirement already satisfied: requests[socks] in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from gdown) (2.32.4)\n","Requirement already satisfied: tqdm in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from gdown) (4.67.1)\n","Requirement already sati