": {\n        \"dtype\": \"number\",\n        \"std\": 1.5106121576728724,\n        \"min\": 0.32,\n        \"max\": 4.53,\n        \"num_unique_values\": 11,\n        \"samples\": [\n          1.43,\n          4.53,\n          0.69\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"Apply_Rate\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"number\",\n        \"std\": 5.543569903295824,\n        \"min\": 4.83,\n        \"max\": 22.18,\n        \"num_unique_values\": 11,\n        \"samples\": [\n          4.83,\n          14.07,\n          7.98\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Analysis and Insights on Linkedin Data"],"metadata":{"id":"EwN1-6Le9Axz"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["After cleaning and examining LinkedIn’s job listings dataset, I carried out detailed data wrangling, feature engineering, and multi-dimensional analysis. This helped me understand the factors that affect Hiring Efficiency (HE) and Apply Rate (AR).\n","The goal was to identify which job characteristics, such as industry, salary, location, seniority, work type, and timing, lead to better applicant attraction and conversion rates.\n","Here is a summary of the analysis done, insights gained, and business implications\n","\n","---\n","#### **Data Manipulations Performed**\n","\n","1. **Dataset Exploration**:\n","   - Checked for duplicates and missing values.\n","   - Created a clean dataset by removing not necessary columns and imputing missing values where necessary.\n","   - Analyzed key metrics like `applies`, `views`, `location`, and `formatted_experience_level` across job  postings.\n","   - Removed inconsistencies through:\n","     \n","     - Filling missing applies as 0 (as `applies` = 0 is logically valid).\n","\n","     - Extracting date/time information from `timestamps`.\n","\n","     - Creating structured fields like State, Industry, Salary Bands, etc.\n","\n","2. **Aggregated Metrics**:\n","   - Grouped data by `job_id` to calculate cumulative metrics for each posting (e.g., total views, applies).\n","   - Calculated `Application Rate` as a ratio of total engagements to total views by `Employment Type`, `Location`, and `formatted_experience_level`\n","\n","3. **Feature Engineering**:\n","   - Created new metric,\n","     - `App_Rate`: Proportion of Applies to total views.\n","   - Identified and seggregated Industry_type from Description column of the dataset for each job posting\n","\n","4. **Top/Bottom Performers**:\n","   - Gathered top/bottom performers in\n","     - Top 15 Companies (Highest Applies & Views)\n","     - Top 15 Job Titles (Highest Views & Applies)\n","     - Top 15 Locations With Highest Applicant Volume\n","   \n","  \n","5. **Inferred Industry Seggregation**:\n","   - Job Postings were further seggreagated in Industry types to find which Industry type were hiring for max no. of applicants\n","\n","6. **Salary Normalization**:\n","      - Converted five global currencies into USD using a dictionary of set exchange rates.\n","\n","---\n","\n","#### **Key Insights and Patterns**\n","\n","1. Industry-Wise Performance  \n","\n","   - Marketing/Advertising, Technology/IT, and Other/Mixed industries have the highest hiring efficiency, with four to five applicants per posting.  \n","\n","   - Retail/E-commerce, Government/Non-profit, and Legal/Compliance have the lowest hiring efficiency.  \n","\n","   - Apply rate trends reflect hiring efficiency; job visibility converts more effectively in certain industries.  \n","\n","   **Business Insight**:  \n","     - Targeted improvements, such as posting time, salary, and clear job titles, should focus on low-performing industries.  \n","\n","2. Experience-Level Insights  \n","\n","   - Executive and Associate roles have the highest hiring efficiency.  \n","\n","   - Entry-level roles and internships have the lowest.  \n","\n","   **Reason**: Higher-skill jobs attract a larger share of interested and qualified applicants.  \n","\n","3. Salary Band Effects  \n","\n","    - Moderate salary bands, between $60,000 and $130,000, receive the most applications.  \n","\n","    - Very high and very low salaries see lower hiring efficiency.  \n","\n","     **Reason**: There is a chance that Very low salary and very salary postings might've had their niche applicant audience.\n","\n","     **Insight**:\n","      Applicants prefer mid-range salaries where job expectations and pay are balanced.  \n","\n","4. Work Type Performance  \n","\n","   - Internship, Contract, and Temporary roles often generate higher apply rates.  \n","\n","   - Full-time roles get the most visibility but convert at a slightly slower rate.  \n","\n","5. Geographic Performance  \n","\n","   - Certain states and metro areas show significantly high hiring efficiency.  \n","\n","   - Rural and low-population areas see fewer applications compared to postings.\n","\n","   **Reason**: There is good chance people who might be looking for a stable change would like to as closer as possible to IT Hub zones if are directly posted there.\n","\n","  Insight: Location greatly affects applicant interest, regardless of the industry.  \n","\n","6. Posting Time Efficiency  \n","\n","- Hiring efficiency peak during:  \n","\n","  - 1-4 PM\n","  - 8 PM   \n","\n","- Weekly peaks occur on:  \n","  - Sunday, Monday  \n","\n","- Worst time/day are:  \n","  - Saturday  \n","  - Morning, 6-7 AM  \n","\n","\n","  **Reason**: People tend to apply in morning as recruiters/HRs are most active at that time as well, afternoon might have peaked because of the time people get in b/w office hrs.\n","\n","  **Business Insight**: Improving posting times can greatly increase visibility and applicant conversion.  \n","\n","**Major Conclusions**  \n","\n","- Industry, salary band, and experience level significantly affect hiring efficiency.  \n","\n","- Applicant behavior depends heavily on time, both by day and hour.  \n","\n","- Normalizing salaries and handling outliers were crucial for realistic trends.  \n","\n","- Jobs offering mid-range salaries and clear, senior roles achieve the best conversions.  \n","\n","- Location is important; postings in states with many candidates perform significantly better.\n","\n","---\n","\n","#### **Hypotheses and Logical Insights**\n","\n","1. Salary Levels Influence Hiring Efficiency\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Job postings with higher salary ranges (90K–180K) consistently showed the strongest Hiring Efficiency, followed by very high-paying roles (>180K).\n","\n","In contrast, roles offering < 60K  salaries performed the worst, attracting fewer applicants relative to the number of job postings.\n","\n","  **Possible Reasons**\n","\n","   - Lower-paying jobs may attract fewer qualified candidates due to compensation mismatch.\n","\n","   - Competitive markets for high-skill jobs push employers to offer better salaries, which boosts applicant interest.\n","\n","  **Insight**\n","\n","  Maintaining clear, competitive salary ranges in the 90–180K band may significantly boost applicant engagement and increase hiring conversion.\n","\n","2. Hiring Efficiency Varies by Time of Day\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Hiring Efficiency by posting time revealed clear peaks:\n","  - Highest HE: 1–4 PM and 8 PM\n","  - Secondary peak: 11AM–12 PM and 6-7 PM\n","  - Lowest HE: Early morning hours (6–8 AM)\n","\n","**Possible Reasons**\n","\n","  - Users are most active during midday breaks and evening browsing hours.\n","\n","  - Morning hours may be dominated by work routines, leaving less time for job hunting.\n","\n","**Insight**\n","\n","  Scheduling new job postings around afternoon (1–4 PM) or evening (6–8 PM) increases visibility and conversion.\n","\n","3. Experience Level Affects Application Rate\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Higher experience roles—Executive, Director, and Senior-level jobs—showed noticeably higher Application Rates, while mid-level positions attracted lower apply ratios.\n","\n","  Possible Reasons\n","\n","   - Senior candidates may be actively exploring fewer but more relevant job opportunities.\n","\n","   - Mid-level roles may face oversaturation or stronger competition, lowering per-posting engagement.\n","\n","  Insight\n","\n","   - Targeted promotion and clearer role descriptions may help mid-level positions improve visibility and attract more qualified applicants.\n","\n","4. Seniority Level Does Not Directly Predict Hiring Efficiency\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Contrary to expectations, Executive and Associate job postings displayed higher Hiring Efficiency than Entry-level roles.\n","Director-level roles sat somewhere in the middle.\n","\n","   Possible Reasons\n","\n","  - Entry-level positions might attract large views but fewer qualified applicants.\n","\n","  - Seniority doesn’t operate alone; salary, industry, and experience level jointly influence efficiency.\n","\n","  - Executive roles are niche and often attract highly motivated applicants.\n","\n","Insight\n","\n","  Hiring Efficiency depends on a combination of role clarity, salary competitiveness, and job type, not just seniority. Recruiters should optimize multiple elements for better conversion.\n","\n","5. Industry Category Strongly Influences Efficiency & Apply Rates\n","**Observation**\n","\n","  Industries such as:\n","\n","   - Marketing & Advertising\n","\n","   - Technology / IT\n","\n","   - Other / Mixed\n","\n","   - HR / Recruitment\n","\n","     show higher Hiring Efficiency, while sectors like:\n","\n","   - Retail / E-commerce\n","\n","   - Government / Non-Profit\n","\n","   - Healthcare\n","\n","     record low efficiency and lower apply rates.\n","\n","**Possible Reasons**\n","\n","- Some industries naturally generate more excitement or offer quicker hiring cycles.\n","\n","- Government/Healthcare may have slower or more complex processes, reducing applicant engagement.\n","\n","**Insight**\n","\n"," - Industries should evaluate job description clarity, compensation benchmarks, and benefits communication to improve efficiency.\n","\n","6. Posting Location Impacts Hiring Efficiency\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Certain states/cities show consistently higher Hiring Efficiency, while others underperform—despite receiving similar visibility.\n","\n","**Possible Reasons**\n","\n","  - Regional job market saturation.\n","\n","  - Availability of qualified talent varies by geography.\n","\n","  - Cost of living differences influence candidate expectations.\n","\n","**Insight**\n","\n","Location-specific benchmarking (salary + job type + seniority) can help optimize postings for areas with historically lower efficiency.\n","\n","7. Employment Type Influences Application Behavior\n","**Observation**\n","\n","Contract, Internship, and Part-time roles saw higher apply rates, while Full-Time roles showed moderate levels.\n","\n","**Possible Reasons**\n","\n","  - Flexibility appeals to candidates exploring options or transitioning careers.\n","\n","  - Full-Time roles may require more experience or longer hiring processes.\n","\n","**Insight**\n","\n","Highlighting flexible work arrangements may help increase applicant volume.\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n","#### **Next Steps**\n","\n","\n","1. **Make the most of the posting time**:\n","To increase the likelihood of applications, post positions on Sundays and Wednesdays at 10AM.\n","\n","2. **Boost underperforming sectors**:\n","    - The government, legal, retail, and educational sectors require:\n","\n","    - Improved job titles\n","\n","    - More precise descriptions\n","\n","    - Increased benefits or pay adjustments\n","\n","    - Increase early-career involvement\n","3. Entry-level positions require:\n","\n","     - Improved keywords\n","\n","     - Increased visibility\n","\n","     - Role descriptions that are simplified\n","\n","     - Job recommendations that take location into account\n","     - Low-performing regions should have their visibility adjusted by LinkedIn algorithms.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"LxUkObi7_X7-"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## ***4. Data Vizualization, Storytelling & Experimenting with charts : Understand the relationships between variables***"],"metadata":{"id":"7P3NDP2UI5G4"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### Industry wise Hiring Efficiency (HE) bar chart"],"metadata":{"id":"TZCOuE7K7Cdy"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Industry-wise Hiring Efficiency & Apply Rate\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# Defensive copy\n","industry_df = df.copy()\n","\n","industry_df['applies'] = pd.to_numeric(industry_df['applies'], errors='coerce').fillna(0)\n","industry_df['views']  = pd.to_numeric(industry_df['views'],  errors='coerce').fillna(0)\n","\n","# Aggregate by industry bucket\n","agg = industry_df.groupby('industry_bucket', dropna=False).agg(\n","    Total_Applicants = ('applies', 'sum'),\n","    Total_Views      = ('views', 'sum'),\n","    Total_Postings    = ('applies', 'count')   # count of rows = job postings\n",").reset_index()\n","\n","# Compute metrics (robust to zero views)\n","agg['Hiring_Efficiency'] = (agg['Total_Applicants'] / agg['Total_Postings']).round(2)   # applicants per posting\n","agg['Apply_Rate_pct']    = np.where(agg['Total_Views'] > 0,\n","                                    (agg['Total_Applicants'] / agg['Total_Views']) * 100,\n","                                    np.nan).round(2)   # percent of viewers who applied (industry-level)\n","agg['Apply_per_1000_views'] = np.where(agg['Total_Views'] > 0,\n","                                       (agg['Total_Applicants'] / agg['Total_Views']) * 1000,\n","                                       np.nan).round(2)  # alternate scale\n","agg = agg.sort_values(by='Hiring_Efficiency', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","# ---- Plot: bars for Hiring Efficiency and line for Apply Rate (pct) ----\n","fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,7)) # Explicitly create figure and primary axes\n","x = np.arange(len(agg))\n","bar_width = 0.5 # Adjusted bar width\n","\n","# Bar: Hiring Efficiency on ax1\n","ax1.bar(x, agg['Hiring_Efficiency'], width=bar_width, label='Hiring Efficiency (applicants per posting)', alpha=0.85)\n","ax1.set_xlabel('Industry')\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Hiring Efficiency (applicants / posting)')\n","ax1.set_xticks(x)\n","ax1.set_xticklabels(agg['industry_bucket'], rotation=75, fontsize=8, ha='right') # Using set_xticklabels for text alignment\n","\n","# Secondary axis: Apply Rate % on ax2\n","ax2 = ax1.twinx()\n","ax2.plot(x, agg['Apply_Rate_pct'], color='orange', marker='o', linewidth=2, label='Apply Rate (%)')\n","ax2.set_ylabel('Apply Rate (%)')\n","\n","# Title\n","plt.title(\"Industry-wise Hiring Efficiency and Apply Rate (%)\")\n","\n","# Combined Legends\n","handles1, labels1 = ax1.get_legend_handles_labels()\n","handles2, labels2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()\n","ax1.legend(handles1+handles2, labels1+labels2, loc='upper right')\n","\n","ax1.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.3)\n","\n","fig.tight_layout() # Use fig.tight_layout() for overall figure\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"B75E-V_3pxGj","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1764436152634,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":729,"user":{"displayName":"Pran S","userId":"15779970413069318186"}},"outputId":"76f04fe0-7d02-47c7-ff42-366a9c3a52d5"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1500x700 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["A bar chart is the best tool for comparing performance across discrete categories such as industries.\n","Since Hiring Efficiency and Apply Rate both represent rates, bars help easily compare which industries attract more applicants and which struggle."],"metadata":{"id":"JDgKVMjl8IOa"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 2. Insight(s) found from the chart !"],"metadata":{"id":"-W1lJOGc8QPx"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["- The sectors with the highest Hiring Efficiency are Marketing & Advertising, Technology/IT, and HR/Recruitment. This indicates that they are better at converting visibility into applications.\n","\n","- The industries with the lowest conversion rates are retail/e-commerce and legal/compliance.\n","\n","- Additionally, industries with high job visibility and demand for relevant skills have higher apply rates.\n","\n","Possible Reason:\n","\n"," Industries with higher digital presence, flexible roles, or fast-moving hiring cycles (Marketing, Tech, HR) naturally attract more applicants."],"metadata":{"id":"8fVHFTHV8Q9r"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 3. Business Impact"],"metadata":{"id":"7IrLPkMs89SQ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["LinkedIn can prioritize recommending jobs in high-efficiency industries to job seekers for quicker matches.\n","\n","Low-efficiency industries may need better salary benchmarks, more benefits, or clearer job descriptions."],"metadata":{"id":"FLi3tIqe9NDl"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### Apply Rate vs Salary Band (Line Chart)"],"metadata":{"id":"kVlLyjBN97PI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["salary_app = df_clean.groupby('salary_band')['App_Rate_Capped'].mean().reset_index()\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n","plt.plot(salary_app['salary_band'], salary_app['App_Rate_Capped'], marker='o')\n","plt.title(\"Apply Rate across Salary Bands\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Salary Band\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Avg Apply Rate (%)\")\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"-MYzYbgf-PnO","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1764436152719,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":89,"user":{"displayName":"Pran S","userId":"15779970413069318186"}},"outputId":"425d037d-a85e-4aa6-9536-cc6a98b31d44"},"executi