estions or location/shift clarity) to improve applicant relevance."],"metadata":{"id":"ZDQQbnLYEevx"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### Hiring Efficiency by Time of Day (Heatmap)"],"metadata":{"id":"gaesktclFJ3y"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["hour_he = df.groupby('hour_of_day')['applies'].sum() / df.groupby('hour_of_day').size()\n","\n","# Convert the Series to a DataFrame for heatmap, ensure it's 2D\n","# Reshape for heatmap: hours as columns, single row\n","heatmap_data = pd.DataFrame(hour_he).T\n","heatmap_data.columns = [f'{h:02d}' for h in hour_he.index] # Format hour labels\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(14, 4)) # Adjust figure size for a horizontal heatmap\n","sns.heatmap(\n","    heatmap_data,\n","    annot=True,     # Show the efficiency values on the heatmap\n","    fmt=\".2f\",      # Format annotations to two decimal places\n","    cmap=\"YlGnBu\",  # Choose a color map\n","    cbar_kws={'label': 'Hiring Efficiency (Applicants per Posting)'}\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Hiring Efficiency by Time of Day (Heatmap)\", fontsize=16)\n","plt.xlabel(\"Hour of Day\", fontsize=12)\n","plt.ylabel(\"\") # No specific label needed for a single row\n","plt.yticks([]) # Hide y-axis ticks for single row\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"KqqUWgHbFIes","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1764436152853,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":133,"user":{"displayName":"Pran S","userId":"15779970413069318186"}},"outputId":"f0e3e038-71cd-4b81-d8ad-83b9ad22cdbb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 1. Why did I choose this Chart?"],"metadata":{"id":"FFGxH2L2GSXu"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["A heatmap is ideal for comparing a values of a single domain across different timelines plus it perfectly visually highlights the performance of the used indicator across the mentioned timeline."],"metadata":{"id":"5QbdrmkHIaY5"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 2. Insight(s) found from the chart !"],"metadata":{"id":"vop8CpnUGDR9"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["- HE peaks at 2 PM–3 PM and 8 PM, showing that job seekers engage most during afternoon and late evening hours.\n","\n","- Early mornings (6–8 AM) show lowest HE.\n","\n","**Possible Reason**:\n","\n","Afternoon/evening browsing aligns with free time after work or lunch breaks."],"metadata":{"id":"uuVshp7XGEXq"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 3. Business Impact and Suggestions"],"metadata":{"id":"R4R2F546GqDE"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Yes, Posting jobs outside the maximum engagement window will result in less view and in turn applies. Recruiters should schedule job postings or boosts during high-engagement windows to increase hiring efficiency."],"metadata":{"id":"_87pEwctGgrr"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"4572f3ea"},"source":["#### Average Application Rate by Hour of Day Line Plot\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Ensure avg_app_rate_by_hour is available. If not, recalculate:\n","if 'avg_app_rate_by_hour' not in globals():\n","    df['day_of_week'] = df['listed_time_dt'].dt.dayofweek\n","    df['hour_of_day'] = df['listed_time_dt'].dt.hour\n","    avg_app_rate_by_hour = df.groupby('hour_of_day')['App_Rate_Capped'].mean().reset_index()\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n","sns.lineplot(x='hour_of_day', y='App_Rate_Capped', data=avg_app_rate_by_hour, marker='o')\n","plt.title('Average Capped Application Rate by Hour of Day', fontsize=16)\n","plt.xlabel('Hour of Day', fontsize=12)\n","plt.ylabel('Average Capped App Rate', fontsize=12)\n","plt.xticks(range(0, 24)) # Ensure all hours are displayed on the x-axis\n","plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":607},"collapsed":true,"id":"FhmKh3f2wlDC","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1764436153397,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":542,"user":{"displayName":"Pran S","userId":"15779970413069318186"}},"outputId":"01d5c740-eabc-464b-f6fa-dcb778f71a0c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 1. Why did I choose this chart?\n"],"metadata":{"id":"c0I-Qjsz25wl"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["I choose this line chart because its the best way to show any instantaneous changes of user interaction across any instantaneous time or any time interval."],"metadata":{"id":"lPU5v2LL49A7"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 2. Insight(s) found from the chart !\n"],"metadata":{"id":"ashOGJa1268l"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["- Application activity peaks sharply at 10 AM, making it the strongest time window.\n","\n","- Early morning (6–8 AM)Shows the lowest engagement, especially around 8AM-10AM.\n","\n","- Activity stablizes in the evening, with mini peaks arounf 8PM and 10PM.\n","\n","- Night Hours (12 AM–5 AM) see moderate but inconsistent interest"],"metadata":{"id":"epeI1H-a5CYt"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 3. Business Impact and Suggestions"],"metadata":{"id":"2ViZztLc27xs"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Yes, better timing of postings do attract better engagement than usual timings and can direct impact apply rate and hence Hiring Efficiency.\n","\n","**Recommendations**:\n","\n","- Post or refresh job listings between 9 AM – 11 AM, especially around 10 AM, to capture the highest application activity.\n","\n","- Avoid posting between 6–8 AM, as engagement is minimal.\n","\n","- Schedule evening re-promotions (8 PM–10 PM) to capture the secondary activity wave and reach late-day job seekers."],"metadata":{"id":"Mr6gq6DY5HEZ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","# **Key Findings and Recommendations**"],"metadata":{"id":"kDJTekDpRs81"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### Key Observations and Insights"],"metadata":{"id":"Z74oCWoGRt6a"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["- Hiring Efficiency (HE) varies sharply across industries.\n","\n","  - The industries with the highest hiring efficiency are tech, marketing/advertising, and other/mixed. This suggests that these sectors are better at converting visibility into applications. Job postings in industries with low HE, such as retail/e-commerce, healthcare, and education, receive a lot of views but few applications.\n","\n","- Salary Bands impact both HE and Apply Rate\n","\n","  - Mid-to-high salary bands (90K–180K) deliver good overall efficiency.\n","\n","  - Very high salaries (>180K) demonstrate an increase in the Apply Rate, suggesting that high-end salaries draw a lot of interest.\n","\n","  - Low salaries (< 60K) exhibit moderate Apply Rates and decreased HE, indicating a lower conversion rate.\n","\n","- Time-of-Day strongly influences HE\n","\n","  - The best HE is achieved by posting between 1 and 4 PM and again between 8 and 9 PM.\n","\n","  - Early morning and late-night hours show extremely poor HE.\n","\n","- Experience Level shows unexpected patterns\n","\n","  - Executives and Directors show better HE than expected.\n","\n","  - Entry-level roles show the lowest HE.\n","\n","  - Mid-senior and associate levels perform moderately.\n","  \n","- Work Type influences overall job response\n","\n","  - In certain situations, applicants are more interested in contract, internship, and part-time positions than full-time ones.\n","\n","  - Full-time roles perform well but not always highest.\n","\n","- Location-specific Hiring Efficiency varies widely\n","\n","  - While some states and cities have very high applicant interest, others have very low levels although engagement at east coast companies were varyingly high than others\n","\n","  - Dense tech hubs and metropolitan regions show stronger HE."],"metadata":{"id":"Yb929z_dR92n"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### **Conclusion**\n","\n","1. The efficiency of hiring varies.\n","How well a job post draws applicants depends on a number of factors, including industries, salary ranges, posting times, and experience levels.\n","\n","2. Timing and salary are important levers.\n","During peak hours, posting excellent positions at competitive pay ranges significantly boosts applicant conversion.\n","\n","3. Industries vary greatly.\n","Retail, healthcare, and education are less efficient than tech and marketing.\n","\n","4. The behavior of applicants is predictable.\n","Higher salaries, flexible work schedules, and midday browsing are preferred by job seekers; matching postings to these trends improves outcomes."],"metadata":{"id":"M8mNe5v8Su7C"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###**Solution to Business Objective**\n","\n","To help Linkedin improve Hiring Efficiency across Job Titles, Industries and Locations, the following strategies address core insights from the dataset.\n","\n","---\n","\n","#### **Strategies to improve Hiring Efficiency**\n","\n","1. **Improve Platform Suggestions**\n","\n","- Prioritize posting recommendations from high-efficiency regions and industries using HE insights.\n","\n","- Use targeted recommendations to direct low-efficiency job postings to more qualified candidates.\n","\n","2. **Boost the Value of Recruiters**\n","\n","- Give recruiters time recommendations (\"Best time to post: 1 PM–4 PM\"). Also, this can be launched as a new adaptive feature that closely observes the apply-time of the applicants every day and should be able to recognize change in applied time of the same to alert recruiters.\n","\n","- To assist recruiters in avoiding low-efficiency salary ranges, provide salary benchmarking tools.\n","\n","3. **Improve the Experience of Job Seekers**\n","\n","- Emphasize positions with accurate salary-band matching and historically high HE.\n","\n","- Increase the visibility of internship and contract positions that draw a lot of applicants.\n","\n","4. **Ranking Optimization & Algorithms**\n","\n","- Ranking signals can be influenced by HE, Apply Rate, and salary band insights:\n","\n","- Increase postings with high efficiency.\n","\n","- Determine which postings will perform poorly and suggest solutions.\n","\n","5. **Advisory System for Recruiters**\n","\n","   Create a dashboard that clarifies:\n","\n","- \"Due to the low salary, your posting has lower-than-average hiring efficiency.\"\n","\n","- \"Applicants may increase by Y% if the salary band is increased by X%.\n","\n","- \"Posting at 2 PM increases applicant efficiency by +40%.\"\n","\n","6. **Platform-Wide Approach**\n","\n","   LinkedIn can increase hiring effectiveness throughout the network by:\n","\n","- lowering the number of low-paying, ineffective positions.\n","\n","- promoting more positions with mid-to-high salaries.\n","\n","- suggesting the best times to post.\n","\n","- improving job promotion in a particular industry.\n","\n","---\n","\n","#### **Operational Improvements**\n","\n","1. **Create a system for tracking Hiring Efficiency (HE-Watchdog)**.\n","\n"," - Create an automated weekly dashboard that highlights sectors, regions, pay scales, or job categories whose HE falls short of their rolling four-week average.\n","\n"," - To spot abrupt changes in application behavior, use anomaly detection (e.g., a location or job title suddenly attracting fewer applicants).\n","\n","   Because of this, LinkedIn is able to prevent recruiter dissatisfaction before it becomes a trend by acting proactively rather than reactively.\n","\n","2. **Engine for Apply-Rate Optimization (ARO Engine)**\n","\n"," - Implement an internal scoring system that assigns a grade to each job posting based on variables that have been shown to increase  Use Rate:\n","   - Competitiveness of salaries\n","   - Type of employment\n","   - Posting time (peak HE hours)\n","   - Industry attractiveness\n","   - Experience level relevance\n","\n"," - Provide recruiters with real-time suggestions like:\n"," - “Increase salary range by 8–12% to boost Apply Rate by ~15%, which will improve Hiring Efficiency for this role.”\n","\n","3. **Posting-Time Autopilot: Allow AI to Plan for Maximum HE**\n","\n","  - Give recruiters the option to schedule posts, but also provide an AI-generated \"Best Time to Publish\" option based on the job's location, seniority, and day-of-week application patterns.\n","\n"," - During the HE peak hours of 13:00–15:00 and 18:00–20:00, the system can automatically queue postings.\n","\n"," - For no additional cost, this alone can increase the Apply Rate by 10–22%, increasing Hiring Efficiency.\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"HFoMemhkVUGl"}}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"/v2/external/notebooks/intro.ipynb","timestamp":1762639108596}],"collapsed_sections":["3Jh7wpEmUfIj","etM5ANHTesGk","ScDsy-O6bpeo","G1pFwzNkb2tj","gkR8u19P704p","tSkwrF749ihW","AJCczQfx21fo","wI5hW8X2ebcn","AN_3P5JOepIe","j_DjNNmg3YZB","LYWc1FXTf-Un","HNmGkMcak_sO","TZCOuE7K7Cdy","kVlLyjBN97PI","H3FjQ8vMEXFj","gaesktclFJ3y","FFGxH2L2GSXu","vop8CpnUGDR9","c0I-Qjsz25wl","ashOGJa1268l","2ViZztLc27xs"]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}